CAPE TOWN - Mamelodi Sundowns sealed a fifth consecutive league title with a 0-0 draw against Cape Town City FC at the Loftus Versfeld Stadium in Pretoria on Wednesday night. The newly-crowned league champions wrapped up the title with four games to spare. The point against Cape Town City FC moves Sundowns to 58 points on the league table with a 13-point margin over Royal AM in second. Cape Town City FC are in third place on 41 points. The league title victory also sees Sundowns claim a 12th PSL title. Sundowns are on course for a treble, having already claimed the MTN8 title. They face Royal AM in a Nedbank Cup semifinal clash on Saturday. -, -12 time PSL CHAMPIONS! #Sundowns #DStvPrem pic.twitter.com/sF5eZLsaFe  CONGRATULATIONS to @Masandawana The #DStvPrem 2021/22 CHAMPIONS https://t.co/RknFQ22Y97 pic.twitter.com/eetqZrodMr  In other results on Wednesday night, Orlando Pirates were held to a 0-0 draw by Chippa United while Kaizer Chiefs were sunk by 2-1 by Golden Arrows. Pirates now sit in fourth place on 40 points, a point above Chiefs in fifth, who have a game in hand.